<1ST_LINE>r a AM-ZZZZBest-Lasko     02-18 0152</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-ZZZZ Best-Lasko,0156</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Pleads Guilty to Helping ZZZZ Best Owner Siphon Money</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man pleaded guilty Wednesday to charges he
helped whiz-kid businessman Barry Minkow siphon off $320,000 from
his ZZZZ Best Co. before the carpet cleaning company collapsed.
   Eugene J. Lasko, 56, of Reseda pleaded guilty to conspiracy and
could receive up to five years in prison and a $250,000 fine at
sentencing March 28
   Assistant U.S. Attorney Jim Asperger said Lasko laundered the
money in Las Vegas casinos at Minkow's behest.
   Minkow, 21, founed ZZZZ Best his parents' garage at age 15 and
built it into a $50 million a year business before its collapse
last year amid allegations of financial wrongdoing.
   Minkow and nine others face trial March 8 on racketeering,
securities fraud, bank fraud and money laundering charges. Minkow
and others are accused of stealing half a million dollars from ZZZZ
Best.
</TEXT>
