<HEAD>150 Missing After Boat Capsizes; Nine Bodies Found</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A river boat capsized Thursday along the
Ganges delta southeast of Calcutta, and 150 people were missing, a
news agency reported.
   Nine people were known dead in the disaster, and a search was
under way for survivors, the United News of India reported.
   The vessel had been carrying about 200 people when it overturned
in the Matla River, one of the many tributaries of the Ganges that
flow through West Bengal state, UNI said.
   Nine bodies have been recovered.
   The vessel was headed from Jharkhali to Port Canning when it
capsized, UNI said. The area is about 25 miles southeast of
Calcutta.
