<HEAD>Woman Faces Trial In $125 Million Investment Scheme</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LISBON, Portugal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 76-year-old woman known as the
``People's Banker'' went on trial Wednesday on fraud charges
stemming from an investment plan in which Portuguese lost $125
million.
   Maria Branca dos Santos is charged with criminal association,
fraud, bouncing checks and breach of confidence for allegedly
operating a huge pyramid lending scheme that cost hundreds of
Portugese their savings.
   Also on trial are 68 other people accused of helping run the
operation.
   Investors poured money into the deposit scheme because it
promised 10 percent interest monthly. Santos was arrested in
October 1984 after she was unable to pay back customers.
