<HEAD>British Jobless Rate Drops In January</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Britain's unemployment rate fell to a seasonally
adjusted 9.2 percent of the workforce in January from 9.4 percent
in the previous month, the Department of Labor said Thursday.
   Last month's figure also was down from 11.2 percent in January
1987.
   The latest rate was the lowest since November 1981, when the
jobless rate was also 9.2 percent. The number of jobless has
declined for 18 consecutive months, the department said.
   Total seasonally adjusted unemployment was estimated at 2.56
million people in January, down from a revised 2.61 million people
in December and 3.11 million people a year ago.
