<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
218,586 cars and trucks this week, up from last week's 215,166,
Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   Automakers produced 245,464 cars and trucks during the same week
a year ago. They were were scheduled to make 133,552 cars this
week, compared with 134,367 a week ago and 171,161 in the same week
in 1987.
   Truck production for the week was scheduled at 85,034, compared
with last week's 80,799 and last year's 73,703.
