<HEAD>Ottaway Gets Additional Posts At Dow Jones</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   James H. Ottaway Jr., a senior vice president of
Dow Jones & Co. Inc., has been appointed to the additional posts of
president of the company's Magazine and International groups, the
company said Thursday.
   Ottaway will report to Peter R. Kann, a Dow Jones executive vice
president, his predecessor in the two posts, who will be freed to
spend more time overseeing the Wall Street Journal Group.
   Ottaway remains in charge of the Affiliated Companies Group,
supervising Ottaway Newspapers, the company's newsprint-mill
interests and certain other investments.
   Dow Jones also announced the appointment of Robert R. Paradise
as associate publisher of Barron's magazine, effective June 1.
