<2ND_LINE>BC-TRW-Conspiracy Plea,0124</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Former TRW Executive Admits Guilt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CLEVELAND (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A former TRW Inc. executive entered a guilty
plea to a charge of conspiracy to make false statements and submit
false documents to the Defense Department, the Justice Department
announced Thursday.
   Patrick M. McLaughlin, U.S. attorney for the Northern District
of Ohio, said the government had alleged that Richard E. Kavicky,
former financial manager of TRW's compressor components division,
conspired with other TRW employees.
   U.S. District Judge George W. White accepted the plea and
allowed Kavicky to remain free on personal bond pending completion
of a pre-sentence report.
   Last week, Kavicky, 55, of Wickliffe, Ohio, agreed to cooperate
with a federal investigation of TRW's handling of federal contracts.
</TEXT>
