<FILEID>AP-PX-02-18-88 2312EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>u f BC-Southland-Dairy     02-18 0288</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Southland-Dairy,0298</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Southland Agrees to Sell Dairy Company</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Southland Corp. officials said Thursday they have
reached an agreement to sell the Dallas-based company's Dairies
Group to MorningStar Foods Inc. for an undisclosed amount.
   The purchase by MorningStar, an affiliate of Houston-based
private investment firm Duncan, Cook & Co., will include 10
regional dairies located throughout the United States, comprising
25 plants and related distribution points.
   MorningStar expects to retain substantially all Dairies Group
employees. Also, the dairies will continue to operate under their
own recognized brand names, including Adohr Farms, Bancroft,
Cabell's, Embassy, High's, Merritt Foods, Oak Farms, Specialty
Products, Velda Farms and Wanzer.
   The sale of the Dairies Group is one of several previously
announced in connection with the December 1987 leveraged buyout of
Southland by JT Acquisition Corp., an affiliate of Thompson Co.,
the investment firm of Southland's founding family.
   In a leveraged buyout, the purchaser puts up as collateral money
that will be generated from the sale of the target company's assets.
   In addition to the recently completed sale of 270 7-Eleven
stores in Houston, Southland has reached agreements to sell its
Chief Auto Parts, MovieQuik videocassette rental and Tidel Systems
operations and 21 7-Eleven Stores in Missouri.
   The company also plans to divest its Reddy Ice, Snack Foods and
Chemical-Food Labs divisions and about 700 other convenience stores.
   ``The Dairies Group has played an important role in Southland's
growth and the success of our 7-Eleven stores since 1936, when the
Oak Farms Dairy was founded in Dallas,'' said Jere Thompson,
president of Southland.
   Southland is the nation's largest convenience retailer, with
8,000 7-Eleven and other convenience stores supported by five
Southland Distribution Centers and six Southland Foods Division
food centers.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
